No direct support. We simulate using default arguments, *args, or **kwargs.

150. Can we override constructors?

Yes. Child class can override __init__().

151. Why doesn't Python support true method overloading?

Because Python is dynamically typed; function signature is not strictly enforced.

152. Can we instantiate an abstract class?

No. Abstract classes cannot be instantiated.

153. Can abstract classes have constructors?

Yes. They can have constructors, but they cannot be instantiated directly.

154. Can abstract classes have normal methods?

Yes. They can have both abstract and concrete methods.

155. Can abstract methods have a body?

Yes, but child class must still override it.

156. Can a child class skip implementing an abstract method?

No. If not implemented, child class also becomes abstract.

157. Why use super() instead of calling parent class directly?

super() supports MRO and avoids hardcoding parent class name.

158. What happens if a child class doesn't call the parent constructor?

Parent constructor will not execute if child overrides __init__() and does not call super().

159. Explain MRO (Method Resolution Order)

MRO defines the order in which Python searches methods in multiple inheritance.

ClassC -> ClassB -> ClassA -> object
160. Explain Diamond Problem

Occurs in multiple inheritance when a class inherits from two classes that have a common base.

Python resolves it using MRO.

    A
   / \
  B   C
   \ /
    D

Python ensures A is called only once using MRO.


